body:
Code example:

```
#[derive(Debug)]
struct Str {
   x: Option<i32>,
}

fn main() {
    let s = Str { x: None };
    let sr = &s;
    let mut sm = sr.clone();
    foo(&mut sm.x);
}

fn foo(s: &mut Option<i32>) {
    if s.is_none() {
        *s = Some(0);
    }
    println!("{:?}", s);
}
```

The Error is:

```
error: cannot borrow immutable field `sm.x` as mutable
  --> <anon>:10:14
   |>
10 |>     foo(&mut sm.x);
   |>              ^^^^

```

This is misleading because the fix is to add a `Clone` impl for `Str`
